Here's the recommended implementation using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** source generators:

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Simulate async fetch — replace with real service call
        await Task.Delay(500);

        Name = "Widget Pro";
        Price = 29.99m;
        IsAvailable = true;
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` notification) and a `LoadCommand` (`IAsyncRelayCommand`) automatically.

**XAML page** — use compiled bindings with `x:DataType`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">

    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name, TargetNullValue='Loading...'}"
               FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product"
                Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `[ObservableProperty]` on a **private field** generates a public property with change notification — no boilerplate setters needed.
- `[RelayCommand]` on `LoadAsync` generates `LoadCommand` and auto-disables the button while loading.
- `x:DataType` at the page root enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time.

**NuGet requirement:** `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0).
